Although most CHIKV notified cases in Brazil were reported in 2016 (

  Fig 1
 ), in Roraima, the majority of notified and confirmed cases in Roraima state were reported in 2017 (5,027 notified cases and 3,720 laboratory-confirmed infections). The number of cases in Roraima started increasing exponentially in January 2017, and the outbreak peaked in July 2017.
